HEADWORD: Razure
<hw>Ra"zure</hw> <pr>(r⟦amac⟧"zh⟦usl⟧r; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Rasure</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of erasing or
effacing, or the state of being effaced; obliteration. See
<er>Rasure</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An erasure; a change made by erasing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Razzia</ent>⟦br⟧
